Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.39,0:00:05.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Bellows!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.77,0:00:08.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got a delivery!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.12,0:00:09.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.90,0:00:11.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.12,0:00:11.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.68,0:00:14.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like you've cheered up some.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.01,0:00:17.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stay sad forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.70,0:00:21.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, Flange and the others \Nare staying in the Sea of Mist.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.30,0:00:25.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Milky Way winds that direction, so if we \Nstay on this course, we'll pass close by.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.63,0:00:27.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We might find out how they're doing, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.54,0:00:30.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I just hope Pinion doesn't mess things up.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.80,0:00:33.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If everyone's safe, I \Ndon't care about the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.24,0:00:34.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.76,0:00:45.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! What is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.02,0:00:50.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's huge! Don't tell me they're pirates?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.19,0:00:52.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.02,0:00:56.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sound the alarm to all ships in the fleet!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.45,0:00:58.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,However, don't act carelessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.77,0:01:00.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Order Pinion to...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.84,0:01:02.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind, I'll tell him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.76,0:01:08.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.02,0:01:11.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Commander Kugel... Commander, is that you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.23,0:01:15.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Long time no see, Ledo.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.62,0:01:17.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's great to see you alive and well.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.16,0:01:19.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You too, Commander...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.77,0:01:23.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I picked up your distress signal,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.20,0:01:27.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but I was on the other side \Nof the planet, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.53,0:01:31.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you'd sent out a transmission, \NI would have gone to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.91,0:01:34.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It was necessary to stay radio silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.83,0:01:36.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you come over here?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.75,0:01:40.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir. Ensign Ledo is setting \Nout to rejoin your command.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.24,0:01:43.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.57,0:01:46.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are they pirates?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.37,0:01:48.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's gigantic! We could be in deep shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.52,0:01:51.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion, wouldn't we be better off just escaping?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.02,0:01:53.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Escape? Escape where?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.83,0:01:58.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, we got the cannon \Nand the tin can on our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.25,0:02:00.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's fire a shot off their \Nport bow by way of greeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.51,0:02:03.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.51,0:02:03.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.10,0:02:10.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Angle of elevation set!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.48,0:02:12.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready to launch!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.04,0:02:14.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.66,0:02:15.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.45,0:02:25.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you like that? Did \Nwe knock some sense...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.81,0:02:34.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.02,0:02:45.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.64,0:02:47.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It was like lightning...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.14,0:02:50.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell do you think \Nyou're doin' to my treasure?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.40,0:02:53.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.76,0:02:55.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The tin can?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.37,0:02:56.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's different...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.23,0:02:59.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ledo! Where's Ledo?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.37,0:03:02.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Ensign Ledo.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.24,0:03:05.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I am now returning to the command of the \NGalactic Alliance of Humankind army.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.76,0:03:08.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! What are you talkin' about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.02,0:03:10.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo! Tin can!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.00,0:04:50.00,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Supreme Ruler of Terror
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.76,0:04:57.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Guide signal received. Now landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.51,0:05:03.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are they doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.08,0:05:07.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Unknown. Conjecture: Collective action \Nto indicate military proficiency.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.31,0:05:10.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,These people are under military command?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.18,0:05:22.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.44,0:05:25.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,envoy from the sky, clad in lightning giant.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.21,0:05:30.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In the name of providence, we wish you \Nblessings of prosperity and peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.22,0:05:32.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's she saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.10,0:05:37.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Speculation: She used an idiomatic expression \Nreferring to a Machine Caliber or pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.92,0:05:40.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is Commander Kugel?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.39,0:05:41.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.59,0:06:01.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.36,0:06:18.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.94,0:06:30.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I beg your pardon for using a holograph.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.53,0:06:32.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Commander Kugel!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.71,0:06:36.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe we're meeting on this \Nplanet! You were safe all this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.44,0:06:39.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Not safe. I have an endemic disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.61,0:06:42.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To remain in a sterile environment, \NI can't leave the cockpit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.40,0:06:44.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.12,0:06:46.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.30,0:06:47.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.66,0:06:50.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Issuing orders from here \Nis surprisingly a pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.81,0:06:52.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.19,0:06:54.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It helps that you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.05,0:06:56.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Will you follow me again?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.30,0:06:58.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.30,0:07:05.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,From Chamber K6821 to Striker X3752,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.39,0:07:09.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,requesting information on \Nrelevant endemic disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.24,0:07:15.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,From Striker X3752 to Chamber K6821,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.42,0:07:19.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,request granted. Transmitting information.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.73,0:07:23.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, we're surrounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.96,0:07:25.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This doesn't look good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.70,0:07:27.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got the treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.56,0:07:29.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure we're gonna be okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.00,0:07:32.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't panic. Worse comes to \Nworst, the tin can will...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.05,0:07:34.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't it leave a little while ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.73,0:07:36.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all over...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.64,0:07:38.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay, calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.50,0:07:40.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't even know what they want yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.89,0:07:43.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're obviously after the relics!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.82,0:07:45.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How would they know about it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.56,0:07:47.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you announced it to the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.79,0:07:50.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How are you gonna get us out of this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.34,0:07:53.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I, uh... Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.49,0:07:55.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this any time to be squabbling?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.03,0:07:56.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You stay out of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.74,0:08:00.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at what's going on around you. \NThen everyone return to your posts!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.60,0:08:07.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.24,0:08:11.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the owner of that \Nweapon is Ledo's friend...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.97,0:08:13.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.10,0:08:16.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then there was more than \None visitor from the sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.05,0:08:22.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But what in the world does Ledo's \Nfriend intend to do with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.77,0:08:25.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Emergency!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.81,0:08:29.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got a message from the fleet!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.45,0:08:32.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Flange here. What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.26,0:08:36.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're demanding to see a representative.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.93,0:08:38.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do they want?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.12,0:08:39.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.80,0:08:42.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They must be after the relics. I'll go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.33,0:08:45.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! I'm the one who \Ncalled the bastards over.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.29,0:08:47.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll talk to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.08,0:08:51.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be ridiculous. I can't give you the \Nresponsibility of diplomatic negotiations.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.31,0:08:53.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.21,0:08:58.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They've designated "Pinion of the \NSea of Mist" as the representative.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.60,0:09:00.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,See? It's my time to shine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.81,0:09:02.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.27,0:09:05.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If {\i1}you{\i0} become a hostage,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.66,0:09:07.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,who's gonna keep the fleet together?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.27,0:09:09.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see your point, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.94,0:09:11.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.97,0:09:17.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,After I brought this fine state of affairs \Ndown upon us, nobody's gonna follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.40,0:09:19.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gettin' what I deserve.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.44,0:09:23.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood. Just be sure to act cautiously.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.14,0:09:26.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. Well, see ya later.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.23,0:09:36.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.53,0:09:40.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're telling you to wait. \NThey'll bring a boat over.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.09,0:09:40.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.58,0:09:45.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"After I brought this fine state of affairs \Ndown upon us, nobody's gonna follow me."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.85,0:09:47.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up, would ya?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.10,0:09:49.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're overreacting. People \Ndon't think that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.74,0:09:50.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.94,0:09:53.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You've {\i1}always{\i0} been a screw-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.53,0:09:56.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody's gonna wash their hands \Nof you over something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.74,0:09:58.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's much appreciated.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.36,0:09:59.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Here it comes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.13,0:10:04.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha...?! Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.80,0:10:06.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.48,0:10:08.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...the Surfing Lobster!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.90,0:10:24.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion of the Sea of Mist. \NThat {\i1}is{\i0} you, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.90,0:10:29.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I never thought I'd meet \Nthe Great Pirate Lukkage here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.85,0:10:32.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You can just call me "Lukkage".
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.22,0:10:34.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And one more thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.74,0:10:38.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For the time being, you'd \Nbest watch your tongue.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.42,0:10:40.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.04,0:11:00.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody looks hard up. Aren't they \Ngettin' enough to eat around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.59,0:11:03.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The weak serve the strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.87,0:11:07.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's divine providence, apparently.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.44,0:11:12.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's their god?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.88,0:11:15.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a lightning giant.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.93,0:11:19.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're supposed to be envoys of \Ngod that deliver holy judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.69,0:11:24.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even as the humans of this planet \Nare blessed with this environment,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.96,0:11:27.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,they're overwhelmed by and live \Nin terror of the Hideauze.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.32,0:11:31.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Our duty is teaching them how to fight
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.95,0:11:34.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and enlightening them about \Nthe dignity of the human race.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.03,0:11:37.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,About that, Commander...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.75,0:11:39.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Hideauze...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.37,0:11:43.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're humans!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.04,0:11:47.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean formerly humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.61,0:11:50.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Commander, you knew?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.19,0:11:54.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Among the higher-ups, it \Nwas tacitly understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.90,0:11:58.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But for soldiers like us on the front \Nline, that's unnecessary information.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.92,0:12:00.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Unnecessary?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.32,0:12:04.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Hideauze just live and \Nreproduce as they desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.86,0:12:06.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They cannot be called humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.68,0:12:08.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.48,0:12:12.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The strong and the weak support \Neach other through rationality.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.32,0:12:17.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They each have their own ways to \Ncontribute and build a society.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.28,0:12:19.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what humans are.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.35,0:12:22.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That may be true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.79,0:12:25.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I brought order to this fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.64,0:12:28.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As a result of the current system,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.23,0:12:32.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,there's been a marked improvement in \Nthe level of happiness of fleet members.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.64,0:12:36.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Request: Definition of \N"happiness" in this context.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.67,0:12:39.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,According to the philosophy \Nof the Galactic Alliance,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.22,0:12:40.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,happiness is the realization
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.54,0:12:44.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,of a circumstance in which the individual \Nrenders service to the entire group
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.05,0:12:47.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and the cost-benefit performance of \Nthat is at the greatest efficiency.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.74,0:12:51.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As such, happiness is commensurate with \Nthe degree of stability of command.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.13,0:12:54.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Agreed on the definition and the conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.09,0:12:57.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.54,0:12:59.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ledo,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.51,0:13:03.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,how about trying to change \Nthis planet with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.49,0:13:17.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.50,0:13:21.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody's here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.20,0:13:33.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.51,0:13:51.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.06,0:13:53.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.34,0:13:55.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.13,0:13:58.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.25,0:14:02.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion of the Sea of Mist, you are \Nwelcome here as a distinguished guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.31,0:14:05.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell? A communication device?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.65,0:14:10.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The remaining humans on Earth require \Nan improvement in technical proficiency.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.45,0:14:15.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This was a test to measure your technical \Nability, Pinion of the Sea of Mist.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.90,0:14:18.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Conclusion: You have an aptitude for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.95,0:14:22.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard that fancy pants \Nway of talking before.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.01,0:14:24.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you're a \Nrelative of the tin can?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.55,0:14:34.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I am a Pilot Support Enlightenment \NInterface System, Striker X3752.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.14,0:14:38.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And what does the great Striker want with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.60,0:14:44.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Your ability to repair weapons that are \Nbrought up from the ocean floor is admirable.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.11,0:14:49.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But only emergency measures are taken as \Nbasic operating principles are not understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.20,0:14:50.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ain't my fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.75,0:14:53.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I'm supposed to know how machines \Nwere put together way back when?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.15,0:14:59.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I am prepared to provide you with \Ninformation on their construction.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.85,0:15:01.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.01,0:15:04.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,With your ability, you need \Nnot stop at repairing weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.41,0:15:08.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You may be able to design \Nand produce new weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.24,0:15:11.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're givin' me way too much credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.01,0:15:15.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Conclusion: You have the ability \Nto learn that technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.27,0:15:20.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My final request is for you to \Nbecome an engineering officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.14,0:15:21.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,An officer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.29,0:15:24.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I ain't no soldier!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.09,0:15:27.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, can you guarantee \Nthe safety of our fleet?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.98,0:15:32.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is valid human resources \Nthat should not be wasted.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.95,0:15:34.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wasted?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.84,0:15:38.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever, if you guarantee its safety, \NI guess I could help you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.66,0:15:41.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have great expectations of your progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.39,0:15:58.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, before you dine...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.83,0:16:01.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It will be over soon if \Nyou do as you're told.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.11,0:16:04.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell do you people think you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.46,0:16:09.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold still if you want \Nto be finished quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.85,0:16:13.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Pinion of the Sea of \NMist to my fellow human beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.81,0:16:17.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Commitment and cooperation \Nare what make humans human.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.81,0:16:21.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,By joining the Flange fleet \Nwith the Kugel fleet,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.79,0:16:25.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,we would acquire even more \Nprosperity and peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.37,0:16:28.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I seek a wise judgment from my fellow humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.28,0:16:30.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is what it says...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.93,0:16:33.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a nice way of demanding \Nthat we surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.49,0:16:34.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet Commander...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.51,0:16:38.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Though we have no choice but to accept...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.83,0:17:01.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I addressing the fleet commander?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.83,0:17:03.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.77,0:17:07.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You have my respect for making a wise choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.50,0:17:11.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I would like to believe that it was made \Namicably. But what are you trying to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.96,0:17:14.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They mean to split up the fleet!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.76,0:17:15.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.25,0:17:19.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Each ship will be requisitioned \Nseparately, according to their use.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.93,0:17:23.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a problem. The fleet is like a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.57,0:17:26.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It only works if we're all together.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.93,0:17:31.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,From today on, you are all in the \Nservice of an even bigger family.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.61,0:17:32.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.16,0:17:36.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Those who comply with \Nprovidence shall be blessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.42,0:17:40.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,However, those who betray providence \Nshall be crushed by the hammer of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.58,0:17:46.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.75,0:17:50.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then get on your knees. You \Nshall receive a benediction.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.68,0:17:55.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,New servant of Kugel,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.51,0:17:57.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,in the name of providence,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.73,0:18:02.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,you shall devote yourself body \Nand soul to the great cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.03,0:18:06.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is totally different \Nfrom the area I saw before.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.45,0:18:09.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Guys that live here must be makin' bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.62,0:18:12.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no money here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.26,0:18:14.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you do without money?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.09,0:18:18.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,According to your work, you receive the \Nappropriate amount of rations from the fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.07,0:18:20.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an extremely fair society.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.34,0:18:22.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fair, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.80,0:18:27.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is your residential area. \NI'll show you to your quarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.08,0:18:38.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.18,0:18:41.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's everyone from my ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.75,0:18:45.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right about now, each part of the \Nfleet is being requisitioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.47,0:18:46.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Each part?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.67,0:18:47.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.82,0:18:52.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you really think this fleet would allow \Nthe consolidation of a potential insurgency?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.48,0:18:55.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It suited you to bring us in \Nand now you talk insurgency?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.60,0:19:02.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, you'd be better off avoiding \Ncontact with your friends for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.64,0:19:06.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.15,0:19:17.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Virus data analysis complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.71,0:19:20.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Running Ensign Ledo's physical evaluation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.54,0:19:27.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Physical evaluation complete. \NNothing abnormal detected.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.70,0:19:33.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All this time, the commander led a \Nhuge fleet from this cramped space?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.81,0:19:36.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't imitate him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.28,0:19:40.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Conjecture: Commander Kugel \Nhas withdrawn into his cockpit
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.59,0:19:46.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,because he wishes his existence to be a symbol \Nand to strike the crew members with awe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.03,0:19:51.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Speculation: As a result, strong \Nleadership will be produced.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.50,0:19:55.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So it's scarier if he can't be seen...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.14,0:19:59.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But is it good to instill terror?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.10,0:20:03.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dealing with fear is one of the fundamentals \Nof the behavior of all living things.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.47,0:20:07.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A show of strength causes \Nthe enemy to be afraid,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.78,0:20:11.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but brings refuge to those who are obedient.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.78,0:20:13.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly, that's true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.54,0:20:17.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Conclusion: As a countermeasure \Nagainst the Hideauze,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.21,0:20:22.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,a display of force is a valid \Nmeans to optimize leadership.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.01,0:20:25.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It mobilizes many people
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.37,0:20:30.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and is connected to the maintenance of a high \Ndegree of community functionality. Plus...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.37,0:20:31.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough already!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.09,0:20:34.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Me too...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.59,0:20:38.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I shouldn't have ever left this cockpit...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.71,0:20:51.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back, Mistress!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.93,0:20:53.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Good work!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.43,0:20:56.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back, girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.10,0:20:58.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How was that Pinion guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.57,0:21:01.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be vulgar.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.28,0:21:02.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.36,0:21:03.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then can we get out?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.99,0:21:05.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's still early for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.28,0:21:10.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that he is capable in \Nhis own way. On top of that...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.91,0:21:13.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...I'm growing weary of \Nhaving too much free time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.18,0:21:19.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Awakening process complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.81,0:21:26.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Communication from Commander Kugel.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.82,0:21:31.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.33,0:21:32.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.76,0:21:35.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to get your help right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.75,0:21:37.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Hideauze?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.42,0:21:41.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No. It's an awareness program \Nfor the people of this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.98,0:21:43.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As you command.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.58,0:21:45.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I like that answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.13,0:21:48.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,With your arrival, that \Nmakes two Machine Calibers,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.04,0:21:53.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,so we're going to carry out a major \Nawareness strategy I've had in mind for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.29,0:21:54.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the target.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.90,0:21:59.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.22,0:22:08.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...Gargantia!
